Q19. What is Abstract Factory pattern?
Abstract Factory ek Factory of Factories hoti hai. Ye related objects ka family create karti hai without specifying concrete classes.
Simple line:
Factory = ek product banata hai
Abstract Factory = related products ka group banata hai

Q20. Why use Abstract Factory?
 - To create sets of related objects consistently.
 - To decouple client code from concrete implementations.
 - Useful when you want different themes or platforms with a consistent interface.

❓ Problem Scenario ?
Suppose tu Car + Engine banana chahta hai.
For BMW:
      BMWCar
      BMWEngine
For Audi:
      AudiCar
      AudiEngine
Client ko BMW ya Audi family choose karni hai.

❌ Without Abstract Factory ?
new BMWCar();
new BMWEngine();

new AudiCar();
new AudiEngine();
❌ Tight coupling
❌ Client ko sab classes pata honi chahiye



ABSTRACT FACTORY CODE :

1️⃣ Abstract Product Interfaces :
interface Car {
    void drive();
}

interface Engine {
    void start();
}


2️⃣ Concrete Products (BMW Family) :
class BMWCar implements Car {
    public void drive() {
        System.out.println("Driving BMW Car");
    }
}

class BMWEngine implements Engine {
    public void start() {
        System.out.println("Starting BMW Engine");
    }
}


3️⃣ Concrete Products (Audi Family) :
class AudiCar implements Car {
    public void drive() {
        System.out.println("Driving Audi Car");
    }
}

class AudiEngine implements Engine {
    public void start() {
        System.out.println("Starting Audi Engine");
    }
}


4️⃣ Abstract Factory :
interface VehicleFactory {
    Car createCar();
    Engine createEngine();
}


5️⃣ Concrete Factories :
class BMWFactory implements VehicleFactory {
    public Car createCar() {
        return new BMWCar();
    }
    public Engine createEngine() {
        return new BMWEngine();
    }
}

class AudiFactory implements VehicleFactory {
    public Car createCar() {
        return new AudiCar();
    }
    public Engine createEngine() {
        return new AudiEngine();
    }
}


6️⃣ Client Code :
public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        VehicleFactory factory = new BMWFactory(); // choose family

        Car car = factory.createCar();
        Engine engine = factory.createEngine();

        car.drive();
        engine.start();
    }
}


